<font color="#FF0000">PEOPLE FEEL IT'S A BAD THING?</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 20:45:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
I'm only in high school- a senior at Versailles.  I never knew there was such discrimination against Vietnam War vets and have been questioned by my teacher if the Wall is really a good thing for our country.  Are we cured of this war?  Are there people out there that think the Wall is embarassing or puts the US to shame?  I think it is good to help those that were not there to relate.  When I visited it I could have cried.  But is there really people out there that think it is a &quot;black gash of shame&quot; or a &quot;black ditch?&quot;  I have to do a report and I'm beginning to discover different views--some of which really amaze me.  Can anybody help fill me in on what is really going on?
<p><code>-- vshsdyakos@mdeca.ohio.gov  (Amy) </code><p>


